6 “SECTION 33. (1) Except as provided in subsections (2) and (3) of
7 this section, the amendments to statutes by sections 1 to 32 of this 2026
8 Act apply to transactions or activities occurring on or after January
9 1, 2026, in tax years beginning on or after January 1, 2026.
10 “(2) The effective and applicable dates, and the exceptions, special
11 rules and coordination with the Internal Revenue Code, as amended,
12 relative to those dates, contained in federal law amending the Internal
13 Revenue Code and enacted before January 1, 2026, apply for Oregon
14 personal income and corporate excise and income tax purposes, to the
15 extent they can be made applicable, in the same manner as they are
16 applied under the Internal Revenue Code and related federal law.
17 “(3)(a) If a deficiency is assessed against any taxpayer for a tax year
18 beginning before January 1, 2026, and the deficiency or any portion
19 thereof is attributable to any retroactive treatment under the amend-
20 ments to ORS 178.300, 178.375, 305.239, 305.494, 305.690, 305.842, 314.011,
21 314.306, 315.004, 316.012, 316.147, 316.157, 317.010, 317.097 and 317A.100 by
22 sections 1, 2 and 16 to 29 of this 2026 Act, then any interest or penalty
23 assessed under ORS chapter 305, 314, 315, 316, 317, 317A or 318 with re-
24 spect to the deficiency or portion thereof shall be canceled.
25 “(b) If a refund is due any taxpayer for a tax year beginning before
26 January 1, 2026, and the refund or any portion thereof is due the tax-
27 payer on account of any retroactive treatment under the amendments
28 to ORS 178.300, 178.375, 305.239, 305.494, 305.690, 305.842, 314.011, 314.306,
29 315.004, 316.012, 316.147, 316.157, 317.010, 317.097 and 317A.100 by sections
30 1, 2 and 16 to 29 of this 2026 Act for a tax year beginning before Jan-
